<html><body><div><div class="story-intro">
				<p><strong>
				
				ELTON John is writing his first book, which will ask why more isn't being done to fight the AIDS crisis.
				
				</strong></p>
			</div>
		
		<p>British publisher Hodder &amp; Stoughton says the book will be  published in July along with an audio book read by the British pop  star.</p><p>Proceeds will go to the Elton John AIDS Foundation.</p><p>John said on Monday the book would ask why more was not being  done to cure the disease.</p><p>He said AIDS "is a disease that must be cured not by a  miraculous vaccine, but by changing hearts and minds, and through a  collective effort to break down social barriers".</p></div></body></html>
